installing nginx controler in namspace ingress-nginx

helm repo add ingress-nginx https://kubernetes.github.io/ingress-nginx
helm repo update
helm install ingress-nginx ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx \
  --namespace ingress-nginx \
  --create-namespace 

here we have installed nginx ingress controler  which creats the load balancer from the service file from the helm, so wne ever you hit that load balacer domanine you get 404 error.

we have not written any  ingress file and added the rules in it ( like domain name and SSL cerificate) and hence, still when you hit the doani name it will showe 404 error 

Since we have instaled Nginx controler throgh helm , After the install, we'll inspect everything that appeared:

kubectl get ns
kubectl get deployment -n ingress-nginx
kubectl get rs -n ingress-nginx
kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx
kubectl get svc -n ingress-nginx    #it give an load balabcer that routs to 404 error becase we have just installed the nginx controler but not the ingress file in our apliaction
kubectl describe svc ...
kubectl get all -n ingress-nginx
